TrapeziumT.scala: Base class of the Trapezium classes, and sequential
implementation.

Trapezium.scala: Basic implementation.

TrapeziumBag.scala: Implementation using bag-of-tasks.

TrapeziumBagObjects.scala: Implementation using bag-of-tasks, encapsulating
the bag and the collector in classes.

TrapeziumBagObjects-Stopped.scala: variant of the above, using Stopped
exceptions.

TrapeziumTest.scala: Tester for the above three.

TrapeziumRun.scala: program to perform a single run, based on command-line
arguments.

TrapeziumExperiment: harness for various experiments.
Usage: scala TrapeziumExperiment <options>.
The options setting the experiment are as follows:
--doLog: do an experiment with a logarithmic scale;
--doLinear: do an experiment with a linear number of workers;
--doBagNumTasks: do an experiment on the number of tasks per worker in the bag-of-tasks example;
--doBagNumWorkers: do an experiment on the number of workers in the bag-of-tasks example, using a logarithmic scale
--doBagNumWorkersLinear: do an experiment on the number of workers in the bag-of-tasks example, using a linear scale.
--doBuffer: do an experiment on the use of buffering.
--doBagBuffer: do an experiment on the use of buffering in the bag-of-tasks example.
Other options are as follows:
--quick: do a small number of samples for each choice of parameters;
--strict: do a large number of samples for each choice of parameters;
--veryStrict: do an larger number of samples for each choice of parameters;
--server: choose the parameters suitable for use on a server machine;
--help: print this help.



Commands to use with TrapeziumExperiment

 scala  tacp.trapezium.TrapeziumExperiment --doBuffer --strict

Add "--quick" for testing

Add "--server" on server

